    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-right has-small-font-size\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/blocks/\">Go to the List of Blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Title block (formerly known as Post Title block) displays the title of a post or page. This block is primarily nested inside a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/query-loop-block/\">query loop</a> block and helps to customize the appearance of the query loop.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"597\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2025/08/title-6.8-1-1024x597.jpg\" alt=\"Title block in the Query Loop block.\" class=\"wp-image-16365946\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2025/08/title-6.8-1-1024x597.jpg 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2025/08/title-6.8-1-300x175.jpg 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2025/08/title-6.8-1-768x448.jpg 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2025/08/title-6.8-1-1536x896.jpg 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2025/08/title-6.8-1-2048x1194.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\">See <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/work-with-blocks/\">here</a> for a description of how to use blocks in general and each component such as toolbars, settings panel, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignright size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"564\" height=\"782\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2025/08/title-settings-6.8.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-16365949\" style=\"width:285px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2025/08/title-settings-6.8.jpg 564w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2025/08/title-settings-6.8-216x300.jpg 216w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 564px) 100vw, 564px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Screenshot</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Settings</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Make title a link</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>It links the title to the URL of the post or page. This enables the website visitor to go to the page by clicking on the Title.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Open in new tab</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>It opens the linked page in a separate browser tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Link Rel</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>It controls the page link\u2019s <code><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Attributes/rel\">rel</a></code> attribute (the relationship between the current document and the linked document), for adding nofollow amongst other things.</p>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"changelog\" class=\"wp-block-group changelog has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\" style=\"background-color:#dce5ec\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Changelog</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>2025-08-02\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Renamed to Title block from Post Title block</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>2023-07-25\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Fix broken images URLs</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>2022-12-12\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated screenshots for 6.1</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Created 2022-03-17</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
